The defending league champions fell behind early on to Romain Hamouma's strike before Moise Kean levelled soon after, but laboured in the second half and failed to find a winnerLyon survived a late Lens comeback to extend their lead with a 3-2 win, with Memphis Depay's double proving crucialPSG did move into second, above Lille on goal difference, after Christophe Galtier's team slipped to a surprise 2-1 home loss to Angers